<BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Elza:<BR><STRONG>Ok since bullseye claims that we have some atention let's make a list for bullseye to send to them with BUGS(not things we don't like, we want, etc) if he would send it in that is(let's hope it fits the storyline to fix them    <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0"><BR></STRONG><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Great idea. This is exactly the kind of stuff we need. I know you have been most vocal in your disapproval, but it is because you care. We need more input from those who care.<P>  <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">quote:</font><HR><STRONG><BR>1) When attacked by assassins out of stealth(with a PA attack) he does not autotarget, even if he did damage to me, i have to select him myself wich is kinda annoying<BR></STRONG><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>This has been brought up in the past. Not sure why it is so hard to nail down. i will see if more work is being done on this currently, or what status it is considered to be in at the moment.<P>  <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">quote:</font><HR><STRONG><BR>2) Same thing with archers, in most cases(not all) when archers shoot their intal shot at me(that bladeturn blocks) they do not become autotargeted and the pet does not attack them<BR></STRONG><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><BR> This one is not going to get such a warm welcome. To be honest, Archers are having a real rough time right now. Their sniping ways no longer kill us in one shot, their stealth is now seen through, and when a pet does stick their day is all but done. They are really supposed to be mage killers, and now it is very rare if they kill ANY mage. They are hurting badly, and as much as I hated being killed by archers, they really have lost any place in the scheme of things. Assassins are replacing them for stealth concerns, casters make their ranged damage unneccessary, etc...<P>Maybe this particular issue should not be this way, but I don;t know if we will see too much movement to change anything to make an archers life harder at this point.<P>  <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">quote:</font><HR><STRONG><BR>3) This happens to me all the time, let's say i fail to mez a goborchend in emain where they are two linked together, i aoe mez, wait for a few seconds and charm one of them. The one i charm stays mezed but the one that is linked to the gobor somehow breaks mez and attacks me, with my pet mezed so there is not much i can do cept running. I've reported this and they said that they have never heard of this before, yet this happens to me EVERY time i aoe mez gobors and charm one, haven't tested on other mobs<BR></STRONG><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Please give me some Logs of this and I will move them over to Pendragon. It will certainly help if we can narrow down if this is MOB specific also. I for one have never had this happen to me, but I normally single out a MOB before I Mez them and wait a bit for the Charm. this way if the first time fails I have 2 or 3 chances to stick it before they move.<P>  <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">quote:</font><HR><STRONG><BR>4) When you put pet on stay and move a bit long away from it the pet status stops updating(if you put it on follow, it follows you but the screen still says that it's on stay, extremly annoying). Health stops updating as well.<BR></STRONG><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Hmmmmm... thought this was fixed a few patches ago. It was a HUGE problem for cabalists and people who summon their pets. I will see if i can repro and report it.<P>  <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">quote:</font><HR><STRONG><BR>5) General pet buffing issues, you all know them.<BR></STRONG><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Our biggest problem: we have the greatest DEBUFF in the game, it is our charm line!<P>Once we charm a pet, it seems to lose 2 to 4 levels of effectiveness immediately. A yellow isntantly starts fighting like a blue, and this sucks. We take a lot of flak for our even con pets, but I think ALL of us know that the CON is no longer accurrate after we charm them. noone is being fooled, we have weakened pets.<P>but as far as the buffing, I am not sure what you mean. Could ya be a bit more specific?<P>  <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">quote:</font><HR><STRONG><BR>6) Getting interupted from a melee in combat mode 10 miles over the zone.</STRONG><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P><BR>This one has a few threads dedicated to it. After the flub at the roundtable, I don;t think they want to keep the egg on their face and continue to 'not see' this one. but again, good logs can only help.<P>--------------------<P>i3ullseye<BR>"You're good, but me? I'm Magic!"<P>Rictus -Sorceror(DAOC)/Rictus(EQ)<BR>DAOC Sorceror team lead...<P>Please visit our <A HREF="http://www.yesterdayland.com/popopedia/shows/toys/ty1050.php" TARGET=_blank>Sponsors!</A>  <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0">
