4) When you put pet on stay and move a bit long away from it the pet status stops updating(if you put it on follow, it follows you but the screen still says that it's on stay, extremly annoying). Health stops updating as well.<P><BR>Yep, happened to me last night while camping at Beno. Stuck my pet in the trees hoping he wouldn't be noticed until after things had gotten a bit chaotic so he could attack from behind. I went back into the keep. He stopped updating just like a pet will do after you ride a horse. Should be easy to reproduce. Just tell your pet to stay and ride off. This happens to me several times a week. NOT a one time thing, and not just one type of pet. Again, should be easy to reproduce.<P>--------------------<P>Elbarad<BR>Percival<BR>Dux Bellorum
