<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
"This one is not going to get such a warm welcome. To be honest, Archers are having a real rough time right now. Their sniping ways no longer kill us in one shot, their stealth is now seen through, and when a pet does stick their day is all but done. They are really supposed to be mage killers, and now it is very rare if they kill ANY mage. They are hurting badly, and as much as I hated being killed by archers, they really have lost any place in the scheme of things. Assassins are replacing them for stealth concerns, casters make their ranged damage unneccessary, etc...<BR>Maybe this particular issue should not be this way, but I don;t know if we will see too much movement to change anything to make an archers life harder at this point."<P>I agree, they're hurting, but I think that they're hurting because Mythic is squeezing them into a spot that no one should be squeezed into.  That being, Sniper.  The problem with Snipers is, for them to work, they work in the extremes.  They're either extremely successful, or extremely unsuccessful.  After all, look at how their sniping has operated.  First, the one-hit kills.  If they kill us in one hit, we feel like they're overpowered.  However, if they don't kill us in one hit, they feel they have no chance to survive; the target knows they're there, and will allready begin taking action to disarm and disembowel the Archer.  So for them to survive, their targets have to die quickly, far more quickly than 5 shots.  Second, their stealth: it's incarnation now is a perfect example.  Archers scream that See Hidden has made stealth useless, and they're partially right.  Against Assassins, their stealth *is* entirely useless.  Against everyone else, their stealth is just the same as it's always been, too powerful and lacking any risk.  So in essence, a Sniper by nature is unbalanced; they must live on the extremes to function, either being Uber or being Gimped.  <P>So the suggestion then is to give Archers a different role other than Mage-killing Snipers.  They need to have a legitimate place, but I don't know what that place might be, or how to begin to get them there.<P>Anyways, that aside....back to the bugs thing.  Here's my brief list:<P>1) "Target allready has that effect" for Mesmerization.  I don't know *why* this happens in PvE, but it still does from time to time.  Diminishing returns are supposed to be the check for multiple mezzing, so I don't what this is all about.<P>2) Like Bullseye said, the fact that our pets power levels drop significantly after charming.  That, in no way, can be anything other than a bug.<P>3) Interrupts, just because it's the single biggest bug that effects all casters across the board (next to uber Resists since that Bard fix a long time back).
</FONT>
