I've reported this bug here probably 3 or 4 times now, and the bug is at least 5 months old.  It's not limited to gorborchends, and it wasn't always the case.  Charm now breaks mez the same way that heals break root (except of course that the mez stays on the one you've charmed).  I've had it happen any time I ae mez a group and then try to charm one of them.  It happens not just with linked pairs but with multiple creatures as well.  You can imagine the result when I tried to charm one of the frostweavers out of a group of 6 of them I had mezzed.  <P>I gave up reporting it because it's 100 percent reproducible, which means it's not some subtle thing they need a careful log to test...they can make their own log of it in about 3 seconds if they either absolutely need one or they care at all (which I doubt).  Did they ever bother to fix the heal-breaks-root problem that they knew about from day one?<P>Tequitus
